\n[/section]\r\n\r\n[section bgcolor=\"#6B98BF\" parallax=\"true\" padding=\"40px 0\" border=\"1px solid #ececec\"]\r\n[raw]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<a href=\"http://www.postgresql.org/about/licence/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://199.103.7.19/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/10-avoid-costly-sql-licensing.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-56\" /></a>\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<p style=\"color: #FFF\">Avoid <strong>costly</strong> SQL licensing by using the powerful Postgres server which runs on all platforms.</p>\r\n[button link=\"http://www.postgresql.org/about/licence/\" color=\"green\" align=\"center\" target=\"_blank\" size=\"medium\"]Learn More...[/button]\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_half last]\r\n<a href=\"http://www.postgresql.org/about/licence/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://dev.grails4notes.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/grails4notes10.png\" width=\"627\" height=\"480\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-158\" /></a>\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[clear]\r\n[/raw]\r\n[/section]\r\n\r\n[section bgcolor=\"#fff\" padding=\"40px 0\"]\r\n[raw]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<img src=\"http://199.103.7.19/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/11-use-true-sql-language.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-56\" />\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\nUse<strong> true SQL</strong> language queries to report on my data — even when it is stored across many NSF databases or servers.\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_half last]\r\n<img src=\"http://dev.grails4notes.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/grails4notes11.png\" width=\"627\" height=\"480\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-158\" />\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[clear]\r\n[/raw]\r\n[/section]\r\n\r\n[section bgcolor=\"#6B98BF\" parallax=\"true\" padding=\"40px 0\" border=\"1px solid #ececec\"]\r\n[raw]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<img src=\"http://199.103.7.19/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/12-security-model.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-56\" />\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<p style=\"color: #FFF\">Mix the mature security model, reliable replication technology for clustered / off-line use, and rapid application NoSQL-style development of Notes with cutting-edge dynamic language technology from coders <em>so</em> good at Java they invented something even better: Groovy/Grails.</p>\r\n[button link=\"http://www.javacodegeeks.com/2013/04/groovy-grails-understanding-part-1.html\" color=\"green\" align=\"center\" target=\"_blank\" size=\"medium\"]Learn More...[/button]\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_half last]\r\n<a href=\"http://www.javacodegeeks.com/2013/04/groovy-grails-understanding-part-1.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://dev.grails4notes.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/14.png\" width=\"627\" height=\"480\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-379\" /></a>\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[clear]\r\n[/raw]\r\n[/section]\r\n\r\n[section bgcolor=\"#fff\" padding=\"40px 0\"]\r\n[raw]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<img src=\"http://199.103.7.19/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/13-avoid-learning-sql.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-56\" />\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<strong>Avoid</strong> learning SQL by using modern language syntax to write natural coder-friendly statements like: </br> <em>book = Book.findByTitleLike(\"Harry Pot%”)</em>\r\n[button link=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grails_%28framework%29\" color=\"green\" align=\"center\" target=\"_blank\" size=\"medium\"]Learn More...[/button]\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_half last]\r\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grails_%28framework%29\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://dev.grails4notes.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/15.png\" width=\"627\" height=\"480\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-381\" /></a>\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[clear]\r\n[/raw]\r\n[/section]\r\n\r\n[section bgcolor=\"#6B98BF\" parallax=\"true\" padding=\"40px 0\" border=\"1px solid #ececec\"]\r\n[raw]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<img src=\"http://199.103.7.19/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/14-professional-database-tools.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-56\" />\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<p style=\"color: #FFF\">Use professional RDBMS database tools such as Navicat® Data Modeler Essentials®</p>\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_half last]\r\n<img src=\"http://dev.grails4notes.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/grails4notes12.png\" width=\"627\" height=\"480\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-158\" />\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[clear]\r\n[/raw]\r\n[/section]\r\n\r\n[section bgcolor=\"#fff\" padding=\"40px 0\"]\r\n[raw]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<img src=\"http://199.103.7.19/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/15-stop-worrying-that-my-notes.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-56\" />\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<strong>Stop worrying</strong> that my Notes views have too many documents in them by optionally eliminating the reporting views and shifting that workload to more appropriate SQL queries and reports.\r\n[button link=\"http://notestoneunturned.blogspot.com/2009/05/how-views-affect-size-performance-of.html\" color=\"green\" align=\"center\" target=\"_blank\" size=\"medium\"]Learn More...[/button]\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_half last]\r\n<a href=\"http://notestoneunturned.blogspot.com/2009/05/how-views-affect-size-performance-of.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://dev.grails4notes.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/16.png\" width=\"627\" height=\"480\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-383\" /></a>\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[clear]\r\n[/raw]\r\n[/section]\r\n\r\n[section bgcolor=\"#6B98BF\" parallax=\"true\" padding=\"40px 0\" border=\"1px solid #ececec\"]\r\n[raw]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<a href=\"http://store.businessobjects.com/store/bobjamer/Content/pbPage.sap-crystal-solutions-2013\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://199.103.7.19/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/16-crystal-report.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-56\" /></a>\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<p style=\"color: #FFF\">Use the industry-leading Crystal Reports® natively against my data to produce nice graphs.</p>\r\n[button link=\"http://store.businessobjects.com/store/bobjamer/Content/pbPage.sap-crystal-solutions-2013\" color=\"green\" align=\"center\" target=\"_blank\" size=\"medium\"]Learn More...[/button]\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_half last]\r\n<a href=\"http://store.businessobjects.com/store/bobjamer/Content/pbPage.sap-crystal-solutions-2013\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://dev.grails4notes.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/grails4notes13.png\" width=\"627\" height=\"480\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-158\" /></a>\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[clear]\r\n[/raw]\r\n[/section]', 'I wish I could…', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '14-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-11-24 11:16:14', '2014-11-24 11:16:14', '', '14', 'http://dev.grails4notes.com/14-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES('406', '2', '2014-11-24 12:13:06', '2014-11-24 12:13:06', '[section bgcolor=\"#fff\" padding=\"0\"]\r\n[raw]\r\n[metaslider id=367]\r\n[clear]\r\n[/raw]\r\n[/section]\r\n\r\n[section bgcolor=\"#f9f9f9\" padding=\"40px 0\"]\r\n[raw]\r\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">I wish I could...</h1>\r\n[clear]\r\n[/raw]\r\n[/section]\r\n\r\n[section bgcolor=\"#fff\" padding=\"40px 0\"]\r\n[raw]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<a href=\"http://www-10.lotus.com/ldd/ddwiki.nsf/dx/Searching_for_Documents\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-126\" style=\"vertical align: middle; margin: auto;\" src=\"http://199.103.7.19/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/01-stop-writing-a.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<p><strong>Stop</strong> writing custom Java or Lotuscript agents to query Notes data in a more complex fashion than can be done with view selection formula syntax.</p>\r\n[button link=\"http://www-10.lotus.com/ldd/ddwiki.nsf/dx/Searching_for_Documents\" color=\"green\" align=\"center\" target=\"_blank\" size=\"medium\"]Learn More...[/button]\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_half last]<a href=\"http://www-10.lotus.com/ldd/ddwiki.nsf/dx/Searching_for_Documents\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-158\" src=\"http://dev.grails4notes.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/grails4notes01.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"627\" height=\"480\" /></a>[/one_half]\r\n[clear]\r\n[/raw]\r\n[/section]\r\n\r\n[section bgcolor=\"#6B98BF\" padding=\"40px 0\" border=\"1px solid #ececec\"]\r\n[raw]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-56\" src=\"http://199.103.7.19/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/02-business-object-model-a.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<p style=\"color: #FFF\"><strong>Develop</strong> a true <em>Business Object Model</em> for the data in my Notes databases.</p>\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_half last]\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-158\" src=\"http://dev.grails4notes.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/grails4notes02.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"627\" height=\"480\" />\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[clear]\r\n[/raw]\r\n[/section]\r\n\r\n[section bgcolor=\"#fff\" padding=\"40px 0\"]\r\n[raw]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-56\" src=\"http://199.103.7.19/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/03-formal-documentation.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n[box style=\"1\"]\r\nEasily create formal documentation in the industry-standard JavaDoc-like format for all of my fields and shared fields on all of my forms and subforms in Notes.\r\n[/box]\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_half last]\r\n<img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-158\" src=\"http://dev.grails4notes.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/03.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"627\" height=\"480\" />\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[clear]\r\n[/raw]\r\n[/section]\r\n\r\n[section bgcolor=\"#6B98BF\" padding=\"40px 0\" border=\"1px solid #ececec\"]\r\n[raw]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-56\" src=\"http://199.103.7.19/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/04-analyze-existing-java-agent.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<p style=\"color: #FFF\"><strong>Analyze</strong> my existing Java agent code to see exactly how many API calls are made to lotus.domino.* API to help me estimate good candidates for conversion to Groovy/Grails.</p>\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_half last]\r\n<img class=\"alignrleft size-full wp-image-158\" src=\"http://dev.grails4notes.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/grails4notes04.png\" width=\"627\" height=\"480\" />\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[clear]\r\n[/raw]\r\n[/section]\r\n\r\n[section bgcolor=\"#fff\" padding=\"40px 0\"]\r\n[raw]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<a href=\"http://grails.org/doc/latest/ref/Domain%20Classes/findBy.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-56\" src=\"http://199.103.7.19/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/05-grails-framework.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<p>Use the powerful Grails framework and Groovy programming language to <strong>interact</strong> with my data in a more natural, object-oriented way (in addition to using SQL).</p>\r\n[button link=\"http://grails.org/doc/latest/ref/Domain%20Classes/findBy.html\" color=\"green\" align=\"center\" target=\"_blank\" size=\"medium\"]Learn More...[/button]\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_half last]\r\n<a href=\"http://grails.org/doc/latest/ref/Domain%20Classes/findBy.html\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-158\" src=\"http://dev.grails4notes.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/grails4notes05.png\" width=\"627\" height=\"480\" /></a>\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[clear]\r\n[/raw]\r\n[/section]\r\n\r\n[section bgcolor=\"#6B98BF\" parallax=\"true\" padding=\"40px 0\" border=\"1px solid #ececec\"]\r\n[raw]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<a href=\"http://www.martinscott.com/struturo.nsf/ID/tech_articles_perf_engr\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-56\" src=\"http://199.103.7.19/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/06-eliminate-unnecessary-views.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<p style=\"color: #FFF\"><strong>Eliminate</strong> unnecessary views from my Notes databases because they clutter my design and slow down performance for large databases.</p>\r\n[button link=\"http://www.martinscott.com/struturo.nsf/ID/tech_articles_perf_engr\" color=\"green\" align=\"center\" target=\"_blank\" size=\"medium\"]Learn More...[/button]\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_half last]\r\n<a href=\"http://www.martinscott.com/struturo.nsf/ID/tech_articles_perf_engr\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-158\" src=\"http://dev.grails4notes.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/06.png\"width=\"627\" height=\"480\" /></a>\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[clear]\r\n[/raw]\r\n[/section]\r\n\r\n[section bgcolor=\"#fff\" padding=\"40px 0\"]\r\n[raw]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<img src=\"http://199.103.7.19/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/07-performance.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-56\" />\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<strong>Performance</strong> optimize the necessary sections of my Domino classic or newer XPages web applications.\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_half last]\r\n<img src=\"http://dev.grails4notes.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/7.1.gif\" width=\"627\" height=\"480\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-158\" />\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[clear]\r\n[/raw]\r\n[/section]\r\n\r\n[section bgcolor=\"#6B98BF\" parallax=\"true\" padding=\"40px 0\" border=\"1px solid #ececec\"]\r\n[raw]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<img src=\"http://199.103.7.19/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/08-slowest-url.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-56\" />\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<p style=\"color: #FFF\">Gain insight into the slowest URLs of my Domino classic or newer XPages web applications so I can improve my customer’s web experience.</p>\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_half last]\r\n<img src=\"http://dev.grails4notes.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/grails4notes08.png\" width=\"627\" height=\"480\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-158\" />\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[clear]\r\n[/raw]\r\n[/section]\r\n\r\n[section bgcolor=\"#fff\" padding=\"40px 0\"]\r\n[raw]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\n<img src=\"http://199.103.7.19/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/09-keep-my-notes-data.png\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-56\" />\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_fourth]\r\nKeep my Notes data in the NSF while <em>also</em> having it available using true SQL served by a true RDBMS. (currently unidirectional)\r\n[/one_fourth]\r\n[one_half last]\r\n<img src=\"http://dev.grails4notes.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/grails4notes09.png\" width=\"627\" height=\"480\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-158\" />\r\n[/one_half]\r\n[clear]\r\n[/raw]\r